===<u>Treinen</u>===
====Automatisch omdraaien bij seinen====
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.1|align="right"|text=(1.1.1)}}
Treinen zullen wel/niet automatisch omdraaien bij rode seinen als er geen vrije route is naar hun bestemming.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:''
{{en/-}}
====Trein acceleratie model====
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.7|align="right"|text=(0.7.0)}}
Selecteer de standaard of een meer [[nl/Archive/Manual/Settings/Realistische acceleratie|realistische acceleratie]] berekening voor treinen. With this setting set to ''realistic'', trains will travel faster up hill, but slower through tight corners.
This option has been renamed from [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches/Vehicles#enable-realistic-acceleration-for-trains|Enable realistic acceleration for trains]].
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:#00693E">'''Origineel'''</span> of <span style="color:#00693E">'''Realistisch'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] train_acceleration_model = <0-1>)
{{en/-}}
====Hellingsgraad voor treinen====
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.0|align="right"|text=(1.0.0)}}
Sets the steepness of slopes, trains will slow down more on slopes if this setting is set to a higher value. It only applies if the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Realistic acceleration]] model is selected.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0%'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''10%'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] train_slope_steepness = <0-10>)
{{en/-}}
====Maximum lengte van treinen====
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.1|align="right"|text=(1.1.0)}}
Specifies the maximal allowed length of a train in tiles. This replaces the old [[nl/Archive/Manual/Settings/Mammoettreinen|mammoettreinen]] setting.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''1 tegel'''</span> tot <span style="color:green">'''64 tegels'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] max_train_length = <1-64>)
{{en/-}}
====Schakel snelheidslimieten voor wagons aan====
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.4.5)}}
Some [[en/Manual/NewGRF]]'s have wagon speed limits to make them more realistic, this option will enable/disable them.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] wagon_speed_limits = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
====Schakel elektrische sporen uit====
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.5|align="right"|text=(0.5.0)}}
Disables electrified railways. The electric trains will run on normal tracks when this setting is active and electrified railways are not available for purchase.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] disable_elrails = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
====Gewichtsfactor voor vracht om zware treinen te simuleren====
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.5|align="right"|text=(0.5.0)}}
The weight of freight trains is multiplied by the multiplier set here to simulate very heavy trains for more realism.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:#00693E">'''1'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''255'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] freight_trains = <1-255>)
{{en/-}}
====Nieuwe treinorders stoppen de trein standaard ... van het platform====
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.0|align="right"|text=(1.0.0)}}
Configure whether new orders will tell trains to stop at the near end, the middle or the far end of the platform by default. Later you can set these individually after the creation of orders.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:#00693E">'''aan het begin'''</span>, <span style="color:#00693E">'''in het midden'''</span> of <span style="color:#00693E">'''aan het einde'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([gui] stop_location = <0-2>)
{{en/-}}
----
===Nieuwe orders zijn standaard 'non-stop'===
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.7|align="right"|text=(0.7.0)}}
With this setting enabled, all newly assigned orders will be made '[[en/Archive/Manual/Non-stop]]' by default. With a non-stop order, vehicles will only stop at the station assigned in the order and will not halt at intermediate stations on its route not assigned as order.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([gui] new_nonstop = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
===Controleer orders van voertuigen===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.4)}}
Enable the option to [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Order review system|review the orders]] of vehicles periodically for invalid orders and other oddities.
This option may be enabled for all vehicles, disabled for stopped vehicles, or disabled altogether.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''nee'''</span>, <span style="color:#00693E">'''ja, maar sluit gestopte voertuigen uit'''</span> of <span style="color:#00693E">'''van alle voertuigen'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([gui] order_review_system = <0-2>)
{{en/-}}
===Waarschuw als inkomsten van een voertuig negatief zijn===
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.7|align="right"|text=(0.7.0)}}
If a vehicle's [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Train income warning|income is negative]] it will be reported in a news message. Use the [[en/Manual/Orders#transfer|transfer]] option in the vehicles order window if you want to set up a [[en/Manual/Feeder service]].
This option has been renamed from [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches/Vehicles#warn-if-a-train-s-income-is-negative|Warn if a train's income is negative]] in 0.7.0.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([gui] vehicle_income_warn = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
===Waarschuw wanneer een voertuig verdwaald is===
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.5|align="right"|text=(0.5.0)}}
Een voertuig wordt [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Train is lost warning|verdwaald gemeld]] if it cannot find a route to the station it is currently heading to.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' 
{{en/-}}
===Voertugen verlopen nooit===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.4)}}
Old vehicles will stay in the vehicle list for you to choose and [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Never expire vehicles|never become obsolete]], so you can now run a Kirby with a Chiamera next to it! When enabling this setting in a running game, vehicles already disappeared from the list will not come back for purchase.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] never_expire_vehicles = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
===Maximaal aantal treinen per bedrijf===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.2)}}
Set the amount of [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Max trains|trains]] that a player can have.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''5.000'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] max_trains = <0-5000>)
{{en/-}}
===Maximaal aantal wegvoertuigen per bedrijf===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.2)}}
Set the amount of [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Max road vehicles|road vehicles]] that a player can have.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''5.000'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] max_roadveh = <0-5000>)
{{en/-}}
===Maximaal aantal vliegtuigen per bedrijf===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.2)}}
Set the amount of [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Max aircraft|aircraft]] that a player can have.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''5.000'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] max_aircraft = <0-5000>)
{{en/-}}
===Maximaal aantal schepen per bedrijf===
{{nl/Kenmerken|Old|align="right"|text=(0.3.2)}}
Set the amount of [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Max ships|ships]] that a player can have.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''5.000'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] max_ships = <0-5000>)
{{en/-}}
===Factor voor vliegtuigsnelheden===
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.6|align="right"|text=(0.6.0)}}
Set the speed of aircraft in relation to rail, road and water vehicles. In plain TTD, the aircraft traveled at 1/4th of ground speed.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:#00693E">'''1/1'''</span> tot <span style="color:#00693E">'''1/4'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] plane_speed = <1-4>)
{{en/-}}
===Aantal vliegtuigcrashes===
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.0|align="right"|text=(1.0.0)}}
Set the probability of plane crashes. They can be disabled if this setting is set to 'none'.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''Geen'''</span>, <span style="color:#00693E">'''Verminderd'''</span> of <span style="color:#00693E">'''Normaal'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] plane_crashes = <0-2>) 
{{en/-}}
===Maak het mogelijk om meerdere NewGrf-voertuigsets te gebruiken===
{{nl/Kenmerken|0.7|align="right"|text=(0.7.0)}}
When enabled, this ''[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Settings/Dynamic Engines]]'' feature allows multiple [[en/Manual/NewGRF]] vehicle sets to exist side-by-side. Without this feature, the maximum number of different vehicles is severely limited and vehicle sets of the same type will overwrite each others vehicles and functions. Note: using multiple vehicle sets side-by-side might result in very high or very low purchase and running costs for vehicles. Mixing wagons and trains from different train sets might result in graphical errors. 
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Aan'''</span> of <span style="color:red">'''Uit'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:'' ([vehicle] dynamic_engines = <true|false>)
{{en/-}}
===Wegvoertuig acceleratie model===
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.1|align="right"|text=(1.1.1)}}
Select the default or a more [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Realistic acceleration]] calculation for wegvoertuigen. With this setting set to ''realistic'', trains will travel faster up hill, but slower through tight corners.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:green">'''Origineel'''</span> of <span style="color:green">'''Realistisch'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:''
{{en/-}}
===Hellingsgraad voor wegvoertuigen===
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.1|align="right"|text=(1.1.1)}}
Sets the steepness of slopes, wegvoertuigen will slow down more on slopes if this setting is set to a higher value. It only applies if the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Realistic acceleration]] model is selected.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''0%'''</span> tot <span style="color:green">'''10%'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:''
{{en/-}}
===Hoeveelheid rook/vonken===
{{nl/Kenmerken|1.1|align="right"|text=(1.1.1)}}
Geeft aan er er geen, origineel of een realistische hoeveelheid rook en vonken zichtbaar moet zijn.
:''Mogelijke instellingen:'' <span style="color:red">'''Geen'''</span>, <span style="color:green">'''Origineel'''</span> of <span style="color:green">'''Realistisch'''</span>
:''In Openttd.cfg config file:''
{{en/-}}

